  %% Diagram 43: Delivery and COD Intelligence Decision Flow

  Start[Order ready for delivery]
  Method{Payment method}

  COD[COD path]
  Prepaid[Prepaid path]

  Risk[Run COD intelligence\ncod_history + anomaly signals]
  RiskGate{High COD risk?}
  Restrict[Require advance payment\nor restrict COD]
  Convert{Advance payment completed?}
  NormalCOD[Proceed with COD delivery]
  Abort[Cancel COD attempt and notify buyer]

  Deliver[Delivery attempt]
  Outcome{Delivered successfully?}
  Delivered[Mark delivered state]
  Failed[Delivery failure handling]
  Reattempt[Reschedule or reassign delivery]

  Dispute{Buyer files dispute?}
  Freeze[Freeze escrow and start investigation]
  Release[Continue normal escrow timing path]
  Support[Support investigation and resolution]

  Start --> Method
  Method -- COD --> COD --> Risk --> RiskGate
  RiskGate -- Yes --> Restrict --> Convert
  Convert -- Yes --> Deliver
  Convert -- No --> Abort
  RiskGate -- No --> NormalCOD --> Deliver

  Method -- Prepaid --> Prepaid --> Deliver

  Deliver --> Outcome
  Outcome -- No --> Failed --> Reattempt --> Deliver
  Outcome -- Yes --> Delivered --> Dispute
  Dispute -- Yes --> Freeze --> Support
  Dispute -- No --> Release
